{{Infobox religious building|religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]]|religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]]|religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]]| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | name = Nagasaki Toshogu Shrine | image = File:NagasakiToshogu.jpg|250px | location = {{ill|Nagasaki City, Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎市|lt=Nagasaki City|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki City, Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|lt=Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}, Kamiyamayacho 19 | iso = JP-42 | latitude_deg = | latitude_min = | latitude_sec = | longitude_deg = | longitude_min = | longitude_sec = | label_position = left | kami = | shrine_Rank = | founded = 1672 (Kanbun 12) | main_hall = {{ill|Irimoya-zukuri|ja|入母屋造|lt=Irimoya-zukuri|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Irimoya-zukuri|qq=}} | alias = | pilgrimage_site = | festival = | ceremonies = | map = }}
'''Nagasaki Toshogu Shrine''' (ながさきとうしょうぐう, Nagasaki Toshogu-gū<ref group=annotation>The official name is "Toshogu Shrine," and "Nagasaki Toshogu Shrine" is its common name.</ref>) is a {{ill|Toshogu Shrine|ja|東照宮|lt=Toshogu Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshogu Shrine|qq=}} enshrined in {{ill|Nagasaki City|ja|長崎市|lt=Nagasaki City|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki City|qq=}}.
Its enshrinement site is in {{ill|Kamiyamayacho|ja|上西山町|lt=Kamiyamayacho|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamiyamayacho|qq=}}, {{ill|Nagasaki City|ja|長崎市|lt=Nagasaki City|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki City|qq=}}. The shrine building is built in a {{ill|Irimoya-zukuri|ja|入母屋造|lt=Irimoya-zukuri|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Irimoya-zukuri|qq=}} style with three ken and one go (traditional Japanese architectural units), and features a stone torii gate at the front. In one corner of the precincts, the {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture Shinto Association building|ja|長崎県神社庁舎|lt=Nagasaki Prefecture Shinto Association building|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture Shinto Association building|qq=}} has been constructed.<ref name=NagasakiToshogu>Harutoshi Takato, "Ieyasu and All Toshogu Shrines Nationwide" Tokyo Bijutsu, pp. 133, 233.</ref>
At {{ill|Chinsei Taisha Suwa Jinja|ja|鎮西大社諏訪神社|lt=Chinsei Taisha Suwa Jinja|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chinsei Taisha Suwa Jinja|qq=}}, a ritual of drawing young water from the precinct's well and offering it to Toshogu Shrine was performed annually every New Year starting from the {{ill|Hōreki era|ja|宝暦|lt=Hōreki era|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōreki era|qq=}}.<ref name=NagasakiToshogu/>
